post_text:
The Show Must Go On: Wizard of Oz

In an effort to bring this show back for audiences, the NL Drama Club anticipates reprising four shows of Wizard of Oz using the same cast and crew as available. We are reserving the calendar dates of November 5-8, 2020 for this event with hope that restrictions on crowds will have eased. Tickets previously sold for the spring performances will be honored for the rescheduled times and new tickets will be for sale in the fall.

post_text:
Class of 2020 signs have been delivered to the high school. There are two signs celebrating each student, one to remain at the school along Route 22 and School Drive. The second sign is for the family. We are looking forward to seeing the signs installed throughout our community. In order to provide a safe pick-up option, these will be located along Airport Road. Families of seniors may come to remove the Airport Road sign for personal use. Signs are first name only or first name last initial. Please be sure to get the correct sign if there are two seniors with the same first name as yours.

Thank You,
Senior Strong, Viking Pride

post_text: UPDATE: Yesterday the Governor announced that the Commonwealth is adhering to the federal guidelines on social distancing through April 30th. In the same press conference, Governor Wolf announced the closure of schools for an indefinite amount of time. Given this information, we clearly know that schools will be closed during our upcoming holiday break. Northern Lebanon will utilize Thursday, April 9 as a make-up day for our Continuity of Education plan. Teachers will still engage students on that date. There will be no online activities on April 10 or April 13.

The Northern Lebanon School District in partnership with Metz Culinary Management will be conducting another food distribution for ALL Northern Lebanon School District students on Friday, March 20. This will include a free three-day Grab-N-GO style bagged breakfast and lunch. However, in order for us to appropriately prepare you must preregister by Thursday, March 19 at 5:00 PM using this link https://buff.ly/2TZWl8z. Due to federal regulations, the student must be present at pickup.

We would like to thank Mr. Rob Best, Metz Food Services Manager and the terrific cafeteria employees who have and will be preparing for this feeding program. Please email Mr. Best at fsmc@norleb.k12.pa.us if you have specific questions about this opportunity.

Registration deadline: Online Registration by Thursday, March 19, 5:00

Pick-up location: Northern Lebanon High School (345 School Drive) by the loading dock.

Pick-up time: Friday, March 20, 12:00 PM – 2:00 PM

How much is it: Free

LEARN MORE ABOUT THIS:
https://buff.ly/2U4arpL

post_text:
Anticipated Bridge Closure

Within the next few weeks the South Lancaster bridge in Jonestown will be closed for reconstruction. Due to the closure most bus routes within the Northern Lebanon School District will be affected and, therefore, times of pick up and drop off will be affected by approximately 3 to 10 minutes. Please click here for information specific to each bus run: https://www.norleb.org/administration/transportation

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact Ms. Alyssa Fellows, Supervisor of Transportation, 717-865-2117, ext. 2529.

Once we have confirmation of the exact time frame of when the bridge will be closed, we will update this information on our website.

Thank you for your cooperation.

Parents/guardians:

In our ongoing effort to partner with you in the best interests of our students, we wanted to make you aware of a social media challenge that is highly alluring for students to check out but is extremely dangerous. Please speak to your children about the perils of searching for the “Momo Challenge”.

The Northern Lebanon School District has taken extra measures to filter and restrict what can be searched for related to this challenge and other concerning topics. The counseling department in all school buildings have been made aware of this.

Please see the link below from the Office of Safe Schools from the PA Department of Education:

post_text:
The @PADepartmentofEducation just launched the Future Ready PA Index = an online, one-stop shop that provides a clear and easy-to-navigate platform for viewing information on student and school success.

How does it evaluate student and school success?

We know students and the schools that serve them are much more than the results of standardized tests. The Future Ready PA Index moves beyond focusing solely on standardized test results to evaluate success by using a collection of indicators, which illustrate academic proficiency, college and career readiness, and more.

Take a comprehensive look at how our schools are doing in educating and preparing students for success by visiting the new Future Ready PA Index: futurereadypa.org.

post_text:
Friday storm follow-up:
On August 31st during the severe thunderstorms, our auditorium and weight room in the high school took on water. However, our staff immediately took action to mitigate any long term effects. Teachers, administrators, and support staff worked together to get rid of the water and start the clean-up process. Our auditorium is open. Our weight room is still closed. All mats that were effected were removed and power-washed. When they finish drying they will be reinstalled and the weight room will reopen. What could have been a serious situation was avoided by the quick action and hard work of our staff. #Vikingproud

Dr. Erik Bentzel

PARENTS: (Updated 2:48PM) The home football game scheduled for tonight is postponed until tomorrow Saturday, September 1st away at Ephrata High School at 12:00 Noon. Due to field conditions, this is the best option for our players and the schedule.

Today, all other home events and indoor and outdoor practices are canceled. We are being impacted by inclement weather inside and outside our facilities.

One event will remain on the schedule for this evening. The National School Climate Center Community and School Collaboration on Bullying meeting will be held in the HS Cafeteria at 6:00 PM. Please join us for this community event, focused on improving school climate.

Most folks don’t get a chance to hear what the kids are doing down in the music room so I wanted to show off our most recent project. The following three songs are the selected winners for our Fredericksburg 5th grade composition competition. All music was composed individually by the students using composition software . I was pretty impressed with these winners.

Ethan Hackman - Untitled (Guitar and Piano)
https://buff.ly/2LepQwh

Chase Stohler – Cool (Flute, Tenor Sax, Electric Guitar, Acoustic Guitar, Tuba)
https://buff.ly/2LgpJQN

Jacob Miller – A crazy Adventure (Piano, Voice Oohs, Tuba)
https://buff.ly/2JkyBaO

Be sure to share your compliments with these individuals when you see them. Enjoy!

Jake Heck
Elementary Music and Band Director
